                    <h2 class="fs-3 text-body">Programme Overview</h2>
                    <p class="fs-5">
                        ILM Academy’s <b>English Diploma Course</b> is designed for learners who want to build a solid foundation in the English language and achieve fluency in communication. 
                        This program is available in both <b>3-month</b> (intensive) and <b>6-month</b> (comprehensive) formats, allowing flexibility for students and working professionals.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The course focuses on grammar, vocabulary building, pronunciation, and advanced communication techniques. 
                        Students gain confidence in speaking, writing, listening, and reading through interactive sessions, role plays, and real-life communication practice.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="fs-3 text-body mb-3">Entry Requirements</h3>
                    <div class="bg-light rounded-3 p-4 mb-4">
                        <p>No prior advanced English knowledge is required. Basic understanding of English is sufficient.</p>
                        <p>Suitable for students, job seekers, professionals, and anyone looking to improve communication skills.</p>
                    </div>

                    <h3 class="fs-3 text-body mb-3">Programme Structure</h3>
                    <p>The English Diploma Course covers the following key areas:</p>
                    <ul class="list-style-one">
                        <li>Grammar and sentence construction</li>
                        <li>Vocabulary and word usage in daily life</li>
                        <li>Listening and comprehension practice</li>
                        <li>Speaking fluently with confidence</li>
                        <li>Writing skills for academic and professional needs</li>
                        <li>Presentation and interview preparation</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        The <b>3-month program</b> provides an intensive learning approach, while the <b>6-month program</b> offers deeper practice and advanced communication skills for long-term fluency.
                    </p>
